rComments: Professor Fontaine was kind, caring and wanted his students to succeed. The grading breakdown may be scary for some (two 25% midterms, and a final worth 50%), but the prof outlines exactly what you need to do to succeed. His class was a nice break from my other courses. He gave historical context on the movie and then we watched it. He's a 10/10 :)

The class was easy, except his expectations for the students were very unclear. He had no actual lecture, he just gave historical context about the particular movie we were going to watch that day. Did not learn anything. the first 30 minutes were spent him giving us useless background knowledge on the film, the rest was spent watching it. Useless.
